# Enrich — Profile (identity & positioning)

Apply for LinkedIn About, personal bios, taglines, contact details, languages, working style notes.

## Target file

`ai-agents/database/profile.json` → single `record` object (not an array)

## Record shape

```json
{
  "name": "Yahor Dubrouski",
  "primaryTitle": "Solution Architect",
  "secondaryTitles": ["Backend Engineer", "DevOps / Cloud Engineer"],
  "taglines": {
    "home": "...",
    "careers": "...",
    "workWithMe": "...",
    "linkedin": "..."
  },
  "bios": {
    "short": "1-2 sentences",
    "medium": "paragraph",
    "long": "full about section"
  },
  "photo": "public/images/yahor-dubrouski.png",
  "location": null,
  "timezone": null,
  "languages": [{ "name": "English", "level": "Professional" }],
  "yearsExperience": { "total": null, "notes": "" },
  "domains": [],
  "workingStyle": [],
  "interests": [],
  "avoid": [],
  "contacts": {
    "telegram": "https://t.me/YahorDubrouski",
    "email": "mailto:yahordubrouski@gmail.com",
    "linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/yahor-dubrouski/",
    "github": "https://github.com/YahorDubrouski"
  },
  "sourceIds": [],
  "confidence": "verified",
  "enrichment_status": "complete",
  "enriched_at": "...",
  "enriched_by": "cursor"
}
```

## Steps

1. Merge new facts into existing `record`; do not wipe unrelated fields.
2. Store **audience-specific** copy in `taglines`, not only one generic line.
3. Register source in `sources.json` when input is a file or long paste.

## Rules

- `taglines` are drafts for agents/site — not auto-published to `src/i18n/*`.
- `avoid` is internal guidance (types of work to decline) — keep honest, not for public site by default.
- Contacts should match `src/data/contactLinks.ts` when confirmed; note discrepancies in enrichment.
